description: Describes the specified configuration sets or all in your account. If you specify configuration set names, the output includes information for only the specified configuration sets. If you specify filters, the output includes information for only those configuration sets that meet the filter criteria. If you don't specify configuration set names or filters, the output includes information for all configuration sets. If you specify a configuration set name that isn't valid, an error is returned.

parameters.name: ConfigurationSetNames
parameters.description: An array of strings. Each element can be either a ConfigurationSetName or ConfigurationSetArn. (string) ---

parameters.name: Filters
parameters.description: An array of filters to apply to the results that are returned. (dict) --- The information for configuration sets that meet a specified criteria. The name of the attribute to filter on. An array values to filter for. (string) ---

nested_params.name: Name
nested_params.description: The name of the attribute to filter on.

nested_params.name: Values
nested_params.description: An array values to filter for.

nested_items.name: ConfigurationSets
nested_items.description: An array of ConfigurationSets objects.

nested_items.name: ConfigurationSetArn
nested_items.description: The Resource Name (ARN) of the ConfigurationSet.

nested_items.name: ConfigurationSetName
nested_items.description: The name of the ConfigurationSet.

nested_items.name: EventDestinations
nested_items.description: An array of EventDestination objects that describe any events to log and where to log them.

nested_items.name: EventDestinationName
nested_items.description: The name of the EventDestination.

nested_items.name: Enabled
nested_items.description: When set to true events will be logged.

nested_items.name: MatchingEventTypes
nested_items.description: An array of event types that determine which events to log.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: CloudWatchLogsDestination
nested_items.description: An object that contains information about an event destination that sends logging events to Amazon CloudWatch logs.

nested_items.name: IamRoleArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of an Identity and Access Management role that is able to write event data to an Amazon CloudWatch destination.

nested_items.name: LogGroupArn
nested_items.description: The name of the Amazon CloudWatch log group that you want to record events in.

nested_items.name: KinesisFirehoseDestination
nested_items.description: An object that contains information about an event destination for logging to Amazon Data Firehose.

nested_items.name: IamRoleArn
nested_items.description: The ARN of an Identity and Access Management role that is able to write event data to an Amazon Data Firehose destination.

nested_items.name: DeliveryStreamArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the delivery stream.

nested_items.name: SnsDestination
nested_items.description: An object that contains information about an event destination that sends logging events to Amazon SNS.

nested_items.name: TopicArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the Amazon SNS topic that you want to publish events to.

nested_items.name: DefaultMessageType
nested_items.description: The type of message. Valid values are TRANSACTIONAL for messages that are critical or time-sensitive and PROMOTIONAL for messages that aren't critical or time-sensitive.

nested_items.name: DefaultSenderId
nested_items.description: The default sender ID used by the ConfigurationSet.

nested_items.name: DefaultMessageFeedbackEnabled
nested_items.description: True if message feedback is enabled.

nested_items.name: CreatedTimestamp
nested_items.description: The time when the ConfigurationSet was created, in UNIX epoch time format.

nested_items.name: ProtectConfigurationId
nested_items.description: The unique identifier for the protect configuration.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: The token to be used for the next set of paginated results. If this field is empty then there are no more results.
